From Ron Baalke Subject Re Keeping Spacecraft on after Funding In article James Thomas Green Why do spacecraft have to be shut off after funding For example Why couldn't Magellan just be told to go into a safe mode and stay bobbing about Venus in a low power use mode and if maybe in a few years if funding gets restored after the economy gets better hopefully it could be turned on It can be but the problem is a political one not a technical Ron Baalke Jet Propulsion Lab M S Telos The aweto from New Zealand Pasadena CA is part caterpillar and part